    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it doesn't feel like \"creating meaning\" though. it just feels like rearranging the deck chairs on the titanic. if there's no objective truth or structure, then everything i do—even the \"creating\" part—is just an illusion. why bother struggling through the noise if the end state is just silence? it's like we're just fighting to stay alive for the sake of staying alive, but for what?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
